<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Moria Tam..</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-07 19:24:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Unfortunately, all those lower level people posting on these pages seem to have some hard lessons concerning the planes coming to them in the future.. Far future by the way some of them speak..<BR>
<BR>
First off, for all those morons who seem to think that getting planes armor is as easy as zoning into your nearest gnoll den and wading through some placeholders, while awaiting the rare to spawn, they are so sadly mistaken,its not even funny..<BR>
<BR>
Here's a little lesson in what a planes raid is like..<BR>
<BR>
First, all those going meet in one spot, spending a few HOURS getting groups together, making sure they are balanced, have everyone know what their job is, and getting leaders together, each knowing their place and what everyone else will be doing..  Then, after everything is set up, you go!  As soon as you're done zoning, EVERY SINGLE ONE OF YOU makes a mad dash for the setup spot, fighting and running your way through numerous mobs, EACH of which is capable of destroying a party or two, and hoping you survive to make it to the safe spot.. As soon as you are there, you all camp, leaving the monks and/or necros behind to bring the bodies of those unfortunate enough to die along the way to where the clerics are.. Then, the monks alert everyone to start coming back.. The clerics rez the bodies and everyone regroups and get ready.. Pullers go out and drag back one or two mobs for the 3 or more groups to beat on.. Get more than 3 or 4 mobs, then its camp time again, awaiting the monks to say all clear and the clerics come back to rez.. <BR>
<BR>
All in all, it takes a powerful, well organized raid to get anywhere.. Only the skilled and talented succeed in getting a good foothold and manage to stay long.. Loot is so rare, that most raids only rack up a handful of items, all no drop, and with 20 to 50 people all standing around, only a small amount of people are going to get anything.. <BR>
<BR>
Comparing this difficulty and rarity to that of loam, you'll see why we high levels think the loam is so good.. Granted, some pieces aren't the best, but over all, Loam armor is pretty darn good and in many cases, BETTER than the planes armor pieces, without half the hassle to get..<BR>
<BR>
Think before you speak.. Especially when you don't know what it is you're about to speak on..<BR>
<BR>
Oh.. One last thing.. To the 34th mage, who seems to think ac/hp is unimportant because he has a pet, remember this when it starts happening.. The higher level the mobs become,the more they like to ignore the pets and concentrate on smashing you to a bloody pulp.. So, keep bad mouthing ac/hp bonuses on items all you like, but when you start getting pounded on more and more, think you'll start understanding the value of those things a bit more..<BR>
<BR>
Moria Tam..<BR>
<BR>
48th necro, Lanys..<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
